[SN]TITLE[SN]
Admiral insurance boss Henry Engelhardt to stand down

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The boss of Admiral insurance is to stand down as chief executive, the Cardiff-based company has announced.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Henry Engelhardt, who has been in his role since the company was founded in 1991, will leave his post in a year's time.
Admiral employs more than 7,000 people and has four million customers. It is Wales' only FTSE 100 company.
Mr Engelhardt will be replaced by co-founder and current chief operating officer David Stevens.
